    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-23T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/341</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-23T15:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8362. War Trade Board [from <persName>Frothingham</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 59. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>.
                    Foreign Trade Department suggests joint conference American, British, and French
                    Ministers, Minister of Persia, to agree upon list of Persian enemy traders,
                    American representative to be guided by your instructions in accepting or
                    declining names. They feel that intimate knowledge local conditions essential
                    and such local recommendations more effective than consideration of evidence at
                    long range. They further feel that moral effect of publication such a Persian
                    list by American Government is particularly desirable in supporting previous
                    efforts British and French authorities in Persia regardless of negligible amount
                    actual trade involved. If you approve proposal they will instruct their Minister
                    in Teheran accordingly. Aside from case of Persia, Foreign Trade Department
                    feels that this procedure might be desirable in Morocco, Liberia, and certain
                    other African territories, also for moral effect. Await your views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
